# 5. Expansion Cards

## Integrated GPU

Built into the CPU or motherboard platform.

Advantages:

- lower power use
- lower cost
- enough for normal desktop tasks

## Discrete GPU

Separate card installed into a PCIe slot.

Advantages:

- more graphics performance
- dedicated VRAM
- better for gaming, rendering, and GPU workloads

The monitor should normally be connected to the discrete GPU when one is installed.

## NIC

Network Interface Card.

Connects a system to a network.

## Capture Card

Captures video from another device.

Examples:

- console gameplay
- camera feed
- another computer

## Device Manager

Windows tool used to:

- view hardware
- update drivers
- disable devices
- check hardware errors

