# 15. Containers

A container packages:

- application
- dependencies
- libraries
- configuration

Containers share the host operating system kernel.

They do not each need a complete guest OS.

## Containers vs VMs

### VM
- full guest OS
- more RAM and storage
- slower startup
- stronger separation
- can run different guest operating systems

### Container
- shares host OS kernel
- lightweight
- fast startup
- easy to copy and recreate
- application-focused

## Docker

Popular container platform.

Docker is not the definition of a container; it is one platform used to run containers.

